2. Lexical Structure

2.1 Character Set

MaiaKoda uses the Unicode character set. Source files are UTF-8 encoded.

2.2 Tokens

Tokens are classified as:

· Identifiers
· Keywords
· Literals
· Operators
· Delimiters
· Comments

2.3 Keywords

Category Keywords
Types int8, int16, int32, int64, uint8, uint16, uint32, uint64, f32, f64, bool, string, array, struct, enum, type
Memory own, ref, mut, rc, weak, consume, defer, alloc, free
Concurrency actor, behavior, spawn, wait, channel, select, async, await
Control if, elsif, else, for, while, loop, break, continue, return, match, try, catch, throw
Visibility module, use, export, import, friend, package
Safety safe, unsafe, defer
FFI extern, @link, @export
Other begin, end, procedure, function, var, const, type, as, null

2.4 Identifiers

Identifiers start with a letter or underscore, followed by letters, digits, or underscores.

```pascal
valid_identifier
_validIdentifier
identifier123
camelCase
PascalCase
_snake_case
```

2.5 Literals

Integer Literals

```pascal
42          // decimal
0xFF        // hexadecimal
0o755       // octal
0b1010      // binary
1_000_000   // with underscores
```

Floating-Point Literals

```pascal
3.14159
0.001
1e-10
1.5e3
```

String Literals

```pascal
"Hello, World!"
"Escaped \"quote\""
"Multiline\nstring"

"""
Multiline
string
with formatting
"""
```

Boolean Literals

```pascal
true
false
```

Null Literal

```pascal
null
```

2.6 Comments

```pascal
// Single-line comment

(* Multi-line
   comment *)

/// Documentation comment (for API docs)
```

2.7 Operators

Type Operators
Arithmetic +, -, *, /, %, // (integer division)
Comparison ==, !=, <, >, <=, >=
Logical and, or, not
Bitwise &, |, ^, <<, >>, ~
Assignment :=, +=, -=, *=, /=, %=, &=, |=, ^=, <<=, >>=
Pointer & (address-of), ^ (dereference)
Range ..
Pipeline | (Koda only)

2.8 Delimiters

```pascal
( )   [ ]   { }   ,   ;   .   :   =   ->
```

