3.2 Composite Types

Arrays (Fixed Size)

```pascal
var arr: [5]int32 = [1, 2, 3, 4, 5]
var matrix: [3][3]f64
```

Slices (Dynamic View)

```pascal
var slice: []int32 = arr[0..3]
```

Dynamic Arrays

```pascal
var dyn: array(int32) = array(int32).create()
dyn.append(42)
```

Structs

```pascal
type Point = struct {
    x: int32,
    y: int32,
}

var p := Point { .x = 10, .y = 20 }
```

Enums

```pascal
type Color = enum {
    Red,
    Green,
    Blue,
}

type Result = enum {
    Ok = 200,
    NotFound = 404,
    Error = 500,
}
```

3.3 Ownership Qualifiers

Qualifier Meaning
own Unique ownership, no aliasing
ref Immutable borrow
mut Mutable borrow
rc Reference counted (shared ownership)
weak Weak reference (doesn't affect RC count)

3.4 Reference Capabilities (Pony-style)

Capability Mutable Shareable Aliased Sendable
iso ✅ ❌ ❌ ✅
trn ✅ ❌ ✅ ❌
ref ✅ ✅ ✅ ❌
val ❌ ✅ ✅ ✅
box ❌ ✅ ✅ ✅
tag ❌ ✅ ✅ ✅

3.5 Option Type (Null Safety)

```pascal
var maybe: ?int32 = null

if maybe |value| then
    writeln("Value: ", value)
end

var val := maybe ?? 0  // Default to 0 if null
```

